Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.00,0:06:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today our problem deals with a platter and a baloon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I let go of the platter and the balloon at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The platter hits the floor first.\Nthe baloon later, falling more slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.00,0:07:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this is the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.00,0:07:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This time I put the balloon on top of the platter.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.00,0:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.00,0:07:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen to the platter and baloon?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.39,0:07:45.68,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(196,241)}1. The platter will hit the floor first.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.83,0:07:45.68,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(200,273)}2. They will hit the ground together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.97,0:07:45.68,white-small,,0,0,0,,{\pos(223,315)}3. The platter will fall, the balloon will rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.00,0:07:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll reveal the answer at the end of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.00,0:07:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, you'll think about it won't you?
